Survival of Provisions/Indemnification
. All the respective representations, warranties covenants and agreements of each of the parties to this Agreement made herein or in any certificate or other document furnished or to be furnished by the parties pursuant hereto (except covenants and agreements which are expressly required to be performed and are performed in full on or before the Closing Date) shall be considered to have been relied upon by the other party hereto, as the case may be, shall survive delivery by the parties hereto of the consideration to be given by them hereunder, and shall survive the execution hereof, the Closing hereunder and the Closing Date for a period of eighteen months, except for the representations and warranties of Seller and the Shareholder contained in Sections 3.6 and 3.20 which shall survive until the expiration of the statute of limitations applicable thereto.
