Section 5  Corporate Governance and Management
Item 5.07.  Submission of Matters to a Vote of Security Holders.
On July 12, 2011, AZZ incorporated (the Company) held its annual meeting of shareholders (the Annual Meeting).  At the Annual Meeting, the Companys shareholders approved four proposals.  The proposals are described in detail in the Companys definitive proxy statement on Schedule 14A filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission on June 1, 2011.  The final voting results with respect to each proposal voted upon at the Annual Meeting are set forth below.
                      Election of three directors for terms expiring in 2014.
Proposal 1.
Proposal 2.                      Non-binding Advisory Vote on Executive Compensation.
Proposal 3.                      A non-binding advisory vote on the frequency of holding a non-binding advisory vote on executive compensation.
In light of the votes received with respect to Proposal 3, the Board of Directors of the Company has determined that the Company shall, until the next required vote on the frequency of shareholder votes on the compensation of executives, hold a non-binding advisory vote on executive compensation annually.
 
 
 
